---
import "../styles/tailwind.css";
---

<section id="practical-info" class="relative p-6 space-y-6">
  <div class="absolute inset-0 z-[-1]">
    <div
      class="w-full h-full bg-cover bg-center"
      style="background-image: url('/images/practical-info-background.png');"
    >
      <div class="w-full h-full bg-black bg-opacity-50"></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold text-white">Practical Information</h2>

  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
    <div>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">Getting There</h3>
      <p class="text-white">
        The Alux Temple is located in Cancun's hotel zone, easily accessible by
        public transportation, taxi, or private vehicle. The nearest landmarks
        are the Mayan Museum and the El Rey Ruins, which can serve as a
        reference point for navigation.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">Visitor Guidelines</h3>
      <p class="text-white">
        Visitors to the Alux Temple are asked to respect the sacred site and its
        surroundings. This includes refraining from littering, damaging the
        temple or natural environment, and being respectful of other visitors.
        Photography is allowed, but the use of tripods or professional equipment
        may require a permit.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
